  "texts": [
    "Distinguished by their lower frequencies compared to the conventional optical spectrum, THz waves are harnessed to detect hazardous substances [128].",
    "Their selective transmission properties enable penetration through materials such as polymers, clothing, and wood, while rendering them opaque to metals, water, and glass.",
    "This capability has proven instrumental in security applications.",
    "The significance of THz frequencies extends to biosensing, as their spectral range aligns with the vibrational modes of substantial molecules like proteins and DNA [129].",
    "In this context, micro/nanoscale devices have been designed for precise detection of DNA sequences."
  ],
